They are also members of collective Boot Camp Clik.

description.plain:
Smif-n-Wessun’s first single, Bucktown became an underground smash, and gave the group considerable hype for their debut album, Dah Shinin', released in January 1995.

Bucktown is a common nickname for Brooklyn. Before Smif-n-Wessun, Big Daddy Kane and Black Moon had dropped it into Down the Line and U Da Man

description.plain:
This is Tek and Steele’s fifth and the least successful single off of the album Dah Shinin' released in 1995. It features Rock (Rockness Monstah of the duo called Heltah Skeltah) and was produced by Mr. Walt and Rich Blak of Da Beatminerz, latter left the producing team 2004.

The song deals of true rap. Tek and Steele showing off their rap skills in cyphers while doing drugs and dodging the police. It is more a representing type of track than a storytelling song.

The song samples parts of Spoonin' Rap by Spoonie Gee.
